@startuml
' Sequence Diagram - Design Creation and Export Process

actor "User" as user
participant "Designer Interface" as designer
participant "Design Controller" as controller
participant "Export Service" as export
participant "Storage Service" as storage
participant "Database" as db
participant "Job Queue" as queue

user -> designer: Create/modify design
activate designer

designer -> controller: Save design (POST /api/designs)
activate controller

controller -> db: Validate user/session
activate db
db --> controller: User/session valid
deactivate db

controller -> db: Store design data
activate db
db -> db: Create saved_designs record
db --> controller: Design saved
deactivate db

controller -> queue: Queue preview generation
activate queue
queue --> controller: Job queued
deactivate queue

controller --> designer: Design saved successfully
deactivate controller

designer --> user: Show design saved confirmation

user -> designer: Request export
designer -> controller: Export design (POST /api/designs/{id}/export)
activate controller

controller -> export: Generate export (format: high_res)
activate export

export -> export: Process design data
export -> export: Apply print specifications
export -> storage: Save exported file
activate storage
storage --> export: File stored successfully
deactivate storage

export -> db: Update design with preview URL
activate db
db --> export: Record updated
deactivate db

export --> controller: Export completed
deactivate export

controller --> designer: Export URL provided
deactivate controller

designer --> user: Provide download link

note over user, queue
  Design Process Flow:
  1. User creates/modifies design
  2. Design is saved to database
  3. Preview generation is queued
  4. User requests export
  5. Export service processes design
  6. File is stored and URL provided
end note

@enduml